    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Hi, I'm Chandra — a software engineer. I design and build
          <strong>distributed systems</strong>: event-driven services, data and ML
          platforms, and the AWS infrastructure that runs them. My hands-on work
          lives mostly in Go, Python, and TypeScript, and these days most of my
          time goes into building <strong>OrbitShift</strong>.</p>
        <p>This blog is where I write up the engineering decisions behind shipping
          software at scale — service boundaries, consistency and failure modes,
          scaling bottlenecks, and the trade-offs that don't show up in the happy
          path. The goal is to keep things concrete: the kind of write-up I'd want
          to find when facing the same decision myself.</p>
        <p>Most posts start as something I had to figure out at work: a system that
          had to handle more load, a service boundary drawn in the wrong place, a
          design with no obvious right answer. I write them down so the next
          person — often future me — doesn't have to start from scratch.</p>
      </div>

